dialog: You regain consciousness, you notice you are in a dark room, alone with a phone on the floor a couple feet away from you.
As you pick up the phone it turns on brightening up your face, you can see the phone has several missed calls and unread texts.
When you go to access the messages they all start to get deleted one after the other until one is left.
Opening the text you start to tear up before starting reading it
The message reads “You need help, we are here for you all you have to do is reach out.
Your hands react to this typing words on their own “I don’t need help, and I don’t need you, I don’t need any of you!
